  "prompt": "What are Dream11 revenue streams?",
  "response": "Dream11 generates its revenue primarily through the following streams:\n\n1. **Entry Fees**: The main source of revenue for Dream11 comes from the entry fees that players pay to participate in various fantasy sports contests. These contests might involve different sports like cricket, football, basketball, kabaddi, and many others. Dream11 charges a certain fee for entry, which contributes significantly to their revenue.\n\n2. **Commission on Winnings**: While distributing the prize money to winners, Dream11 takes a small commission from the winnings. This helps in generating additional revenue.\n\n3. **Advertising and Sponsorship**: Dream11 leverages its platform to display advertisements and attract sponsorship deals. Brands and companies pay to advertise their products and services on Dream11's app and website, providing another revenue stream.\n\n4. **In-App Purchases**: Although this is not a major part of Dream11\u2019s revenue, some aspects of the app might offer in-app purchases or premium features that users can buy for enhanced experiences.\n\n5. **Partnerships and Collaborations**: Dream11 often collaborates with various sports leagues, teams, or events for partnerships which can include sponsorship deals, promotions, and exclusive content. These partnerships can also contribute to Dream11's revenue.\n\nBy diversifying their revenue streams, Dream11 maintains a robust financial model that supports its growth and operations in the competitive fantasy sports market.",
